

1)Install java 8 or 11 
2)Download and install jenkins , url :https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/
3)Got to browser at url : localhst:8080
4)setup jenkins account 
5)Install - docker, nodejs plugin
6)Add git, java(ex : usr/lib/jvm), docker, node config/path and save, apply
7)Add jenkins user to docker group for acces permission. 
    command: sudo usermod -a -G docker jenkins
8)Check whether user jenkins is added to docker group
    command: cat /etc/group | grep 'docker'
9)Creating Docker Private Registry:
    command to run private docker registry image:
        docker run -d -p 7009:5000 --restart always --name registry -v registrydata:/data registry:2.7.1
10)Setting our pc ip to private registry docker.service file :
    a)service docker status -> under this at loaded tage not the path of docker.service (it would be /lib/systemd/system/docker.service)
    b) Now open that file : sudo nano <that path>
    c)At ExecStart, /usr/bin/dockerd --insecure-registry 192.168.43.160:7009 -H fd:// --containerd=/run/containerd/containerd.sock
12)Now, restart docker :
    command : 
        a) sudo systemctl daemon-reload
        b) service docker restart
        c) systemctl status docker
13) Make Sure the Ip of docker registry is corrct in jenkins file

